== 非专职吞噬细胞 ==
走向死亡的细胞以及侵入體內的外來生物也能由「专职」吞噬细胞以外的细胞吞食<ref name="pmid18451871">{{cite journal
| author = Birge RB, Ucker DS
| title = Innate apoptotic immunity: the calming touch of death | journal = Cell Death Differ. | volume = 15 | issue = 7 | pages = 1096–1102 |date=2008-07 | pmid = 18451871 | doi = 10.1038/cdd.2008.58
| ref = harv | last2 = Ucker }}</ref>，这些细胞包括[[上皮细胞|上皮细胞]]、[[内皮细胞|内皮细胞]]、[[成纤维细胞|成纤维细胞]]，以及[[間質幹細胞|間質幹細胞]]。將它們称为非专职吞噬细胞（non-professional phagocytes）是為了强调其與专职吞噬细胞的不同，吞噬不是它们最主要的功能<ref name="pmid11083817">{{cite journal| author = Couzinet S, Cejas E, Schittny J, Deplazes P, Weber R, Zimmerli S| title = Phagocytic uptake of ''Encephalitozoon cuniculi'' by nonprofessional phagocytes| journal = Infect. Immun.| volume = 68| issue = 12| pages = 6939–45| date = 2000-12| pmid = 11083817| pmc = 97802| url = http://iai.asm.org/cgi/pmidlookup?view=long&pmid=11083817| doi = 10.1128/IAI.68.12.6939-6945.2000| ref = harv| last2 = Cejas| last3 = Schittny| last4 = Deplazes| last5 = Weber| last6 = Zimmerli| accessdate = 2014-12-19| archive-date = 2020-06-08| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200608213530/https://iai.asm.org/content/68/12/6939.long| dead-url = no}}</ref>。举例来说，成纤维细胞在疤痕的重塑过程中會吞噬[[膠原蛋白|膠原蛋白]]，同時也會嘗試消化外来颗粒<ref>{{Cite journal |title=Involvement of actin filaments and integrins in the binding step in collagen phagocytosis by human fibroblasts |author=Segal G, Lee W, Arora PD, McKee M, Downey G, McCulloch CA |last2=Lee |date=200101 |journal=Journal of Cell Science |issue=Pt 1 |volume=114 |pages=119–129 |pmid=11112696 |last3=Arora |last4=McKee |last5=Downey |last6=McCulloch}}</ref>。

非专职吞噬细胞能吞噬的颗粒种类比专职吞噬细胞少，这是因为它们缺乏高效的吞噬受体──特別是[[调理素|调理素]]受體。调理素是指由免疫系統產生而能協助吞噬的物質，它們通常是能与入侵物质结合的抗体或补体<ref name= something/>。另外，大多数的非专职吞噬细胞都不能产生用以殺滅的活性氧物質<ref name="pmid14732160">{{Cite journal |title=Professional and non-professional phagocytes: an introduction |author=Rabinovitch M |url=http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0962892400889552 |date=1995-03 |journal=Trends Cell Biol. |accessdate=2014-12-19 |issue=3 |doi=10.1016/S0962-8924(00)88955-2 |volume=5 |pages=85–87 |pmid=14732160 |ref=harv |archive-date=2019-03-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190304143125/http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0962892400889552 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

